						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into a water-sluice called Raṅgappabhāvi.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka [163]6, <hi rend="italic">Kshaya, Jyēshṭha,</hi> śu. [15]. The Śaka and cyclic years do not correspond.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to refer to the construction of a well and to the endowment in the shape of land made for its upkeep, by purchase from Annapā and Tippā-bhaṭla in an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> (name lost).</p>						

						</summary>
